## Collapsible/Expandable Components

### Sidebar Pattern

When creating collapsible components like sidebars:

**Key Implementation Points:**

1. **State Management**: Use local state for collapsed/expanded state
2. **Conditional Rendering**: Hide labels, text when collapsed
3. **Animation**: Use Framer Motion for smooth transitions
4. **Accessibility**: Add proper aria-labels and titles

**Example Pattern:**
```typescript
const [isExpanded, setIsExpanded] = useState(true)

// Animate width
<motion.aside
    animate={{ width: isExpanded ? 280 : 60 }}
    transition={{ duration: 0.3, ease: 'easeInOut' }}
    className="..."
>

// Conditional rendering
{!isCollapsed && <p>{label}</p>}

// Expand button when collapsed
{!isExpanded && (
    <button onClick={() => setIsExpanded(true)}>
        <Icon name="expand" />
    </button>
)}
```

### Component Hierarchy

When passing collapsed state through component hierarchy:

```typescript
// Template component
<MoleculeSidebarNavGroup
    title="Dashboard"
    items={items}
    isCollapsed={!isExpanded}
/>

// Molecule component
const MoleculeSidebarNavGroup = ({ isCollapsed, items }) => (
    items.map(item => (
        <MoleculeMenuItem
            {...item}
            isCollapsed={isCollapsed}
        />
    ))
)

// Atom usage
{!isCollapsed && <span>{label}</span>}
```

