## Animation Patterns with Framer Motion

### Common Animation Use Cases

#### 1. Hover Effects
```typescript
import { motion } from 'framer-motion'

<motion.button
    whileHover={{ scale: 1.02 }}
    whileTap={{ scale: 0.98 }}
    onClick={handleClick}
>
    {children}
</motion.button>
```

#### 2. Width Transitions
```typescript
<motion.aside
    animate={{ width: isExpanded ? 280 : 60 }}
    transition={{ duration: 0.3, ease: 'easeInOut' }}
>
```

#### 3. Opacity Fades
```typescript
<motion.div
    animate={{ opacity: isVisible ? 1 : 0 }}
    transition={{ duration: 0.3 }}
>
```

#### 4. Conditional Animations
```typescript
import { AnimatePresence } from 'framer-motion'

<AnimatePresence>
    {isExpanded && (
        <motion.div
            initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 10 }}
            animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
            exit={{ opacity: 0, y: 10 }}
            transition={{ duration: 0.2 }}
        >
            {content}
        </motion.div>
    )}
</AnimatePresence>
```

### Animation Best Practices

- ✅ Use `initial={false}` to skip initial animation
- ✅ Set appropriate `duration` (typically 0.2-0.3s)
- ✅ Use `ease: 'easeInOut'` for natural feel
- ✅ Animate size/opacity for smooth transitions
- ✅ Use `AnimatePresence` for mount/unmount animations

