## Color Management and Theme Usage

### Using Theme Colors

**NEVER** use hardcoded hex colors. Always use Tailwind classes that reference `colors.ts`:

```typescript
// ❌ Bad - Hardcoded colors
<div className="border-[#d4d4d4] text-[#0A0A0A] bg-[#f5f5f5]">

// ✅ Good - Theme colors
<div className="border-neutral-300 text-neutral-950 bg-neutral-100">
```

### Color Mapping

From `src/theme/colors.ts` to Tailwind classes:

| Color       | Hex     | Tailwind Class        |
| ----------- | ------- | --------------------- |
| neutral.950 | #0A0A0A | `text-neutral-950`    |
| neutral.600 | #525252 | `text-neutral-600`    |
| neutral.300 | #d4d4d4 | `border-neutral-300`  |
| neutral.200 | #e5e5e5 | `border-neutral-200`  |
| neutral.100 | #f5f5f5 | `bg-neutral-100`      |
| neutral.50  | #fafafa | `hover:bg-neutral-50` |

### Converting Colors

When updating components:
1. Replace hardcoded hex with Tailwind class
2. Check `colors.ts` for matching color
3. Use appropriate shade (50-950)
4. Test visual consistency

**Migration Example:**
```typescript
// Before
<div className="bg-[#f5f5f5] text-[#0A0A0A]">
    <p className="text-gray-600">Text</p>
</div>

// After
<div className="bg-neutral-100 text-neutral-950">
    <p className="text-neutral-600">Text</p>
</div>
```

